{{ja-kanjitab|おぼろ|yomi=k}}

Appears to be {{suffix|ja|sort=おぼろ|凡|tr1=obo|t1=[[dim]], [[faint]]; [[hazy]], [[indistinct]]|ろ|tr2=ro|pos2=suffix apparently indicating general location or time, as in {{m|ja|所|tr=tokoro||place}}, {{m|ja|頃|tr=koro||around (a specific time)}}; compare {{ja-r|ら}}}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJS">{{R:Daijisen}}</ref>

The food-related senses may come from the way these dishes involve breaking up the main ingredients into smaller indistinct pieces.

First attested in ''{{w|The Tale of Ise}}'' from the early 900s.<ref name="KDJ"/>

